description:
Application under s.106A Town and Country Planning Act 1990 to vary legal agreement dated 2 January 2008 for planning permission ref.2006/4533 (as varied by six Deeds of Variation)

Variation of legal agreement to include:
- Modification of 'Public Access Areas' to make Ensign Garden and Genoa Garden 'Private Amenity Areas' with no public access;
- removal of 'Public Right of Way' and 'Access Point 9' (Mendip Gate) east of Ensign House and amalgamation of land within Ensign Garden;
- Modify public access to courtyards east of Jasmine House and west of Discovery House from between 9am and half an hour after sunset each day to between 6am and 10pm each day; and
- Replacement of Plan D [Public Access Areas] and Plan E [Public Rights of Way]; replacement of clause 16.1.2 [Public Access and Phasing], deletion of clause 16.7 [access at Mendip Gate] and clause 31 [option for dedication of identified land for public use].
